rimitives — see the Radix UI documentation for their props."],[46,"`AvatarFallback` renders when the image is unavailable — typically the user's initials."],[47,"`AvatarGroup` stacks several avatars into an overlapping row."],[69,"`BadgeActionButton` adds a trailing button."],[567,"`bg-green-600`"],[584,"`bg-primary`"],[572,"`bg-subtle`"],[568,"`border-blue-700` etc."],[586,"`border-default`"],[573,"`border-subtle` etc."],[83,"`Breadcrumb`, `BreadcrumbLink`, and `BreadcrumbPage` render a `<nav>`, `<a>`, and `<span>`. Each accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[100,"`ButtonToolbar` combines multiple groups into a single toolbar."],[142,"`CardGroup` joins cards into an attached row."],[143,"`CardHeader`, `CardBody`, `CardFooter`, `CardTitle`, `CardSubtitle`, `CardText`, `CardImageOverlay`, and `CardGroup` are layout wrappers. Each accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[138,"`CardImage` places an image whose `position` controls which corners are rounded."],[139,"`CardImageOverlay` lays the `CardBody` over the image."],[170,"`Collapsible` lets users show and hide content with a trigger."],[633,"`DarkThemeToggle` switches between light and dark mode, persists the choice, and keeps all tabs in sync."],[207,"`DrawerBody` grows to fill the panel and scrolls its own overflow while the header stays pinned."],[221,"`DropdownMenuGroup` bundles related items under a `DropdownMenuLabel` section header."],[224,"`DropdownMenuItemText` displays non-interactive text in a menu."],[226,"`DropdownMenuItemText` renders non-interactive copy as a `<span>` and accepts a `className`."],[470,"`FormField`, `FormLabel`, `InputIcon`, `InputIconStart`, and `InputIconEnd` are\nlayout wrappers. Each accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[501,"`InputGroupText` is an addon wrapper. It accepts `asChild` and `className`."],[468,"`InputIcon` adds `InputIconStart` and/or `InputIconEnd` to an input while automatically adjusting the input padding."],[248,"`ListText` provides title and subtitle text for composing richer item layouts."],[300,"`NavbarBrand` and `NavbarText` are layout wrappers that accept only `asChild` and `className`. `NavbarTogglerIcon` renders the default hamburger glyph and accepts standard `svg` props."],[298,"`NavbarCollapse` wraps the Radix Collapsible content; for its shared props, see the Radix UI documentation."],[295,"`NavbarText` renders non-link content such as a signed-in label."],[291,"`NavbarToggle` and `NavbarCollapse` hide the menu behind a toggle below the `expand` breakpoint."],[299,"`NavbarToggle` wraps the Radix Collapsible trigger. For detailed usage guidelines, see the Radix UI documentation."],[270,"`NavItem` is a layout wrapper that accepts only `asChild` and `className`."],[737,"`p-(--my-padding)` — a custom CSS property"],[738,"`p-[12px]` — an arbitrary value"],[735,"`p-4` — a number, multiplied by the `--spacing` scale (where applicable)"],[736,"`p-px` — a fixed `1px` value"],[318,"`Pagination` is an accessible `<nav>` wrapping a `PaginationContent` list of `PaginationItem`s, with the current page marked by `active`."],[337,"`PopoverClose` dismisses the popover from within the content."],[340,"`PopoverHeader` and `PopoverBody` render the popover's header and body regions. Each accepts a `className`."],[516,"`RadioGroup` groups related radio buttons and manages the selected value."],[374,"`TableCaption` renders a caption above the table."],[375,"`TableFooter` renders a summary row group at the bottom of the table."],[376,"`TableHeader`, `TableBody`, `TableFooter`, `TableHead`, and `TableCaption` render their native table elements and accept only `className` alongside their standard element props."],[390,"`TabsList` uses the bordered style by default. Set `defaultValue` to select the initial tab."],[585,"`text-muted`"],[571,"`text-primary`"],[566,"`text-red-500`"],[615,"1\\. Custom dark mode selector"],[749,"1\\. Install Tailwind CSS"],[750,"2\\. Install Hummingbird React"],[616,"2\\. Set the initial theme"],[617,"3\\. Add a the